screens.screen_desc: The screenshot displays a shopping app interface featuring various product categories. At the top, there's a search bar and a section titled "Kitchen favorites under $50," accompanied by images of kitchen items like a whisk and wooden utensils. Below, there are sections for "Carry-on luggage," "Computer keyboards," and "Glow up under $25," showcasing relevant products. Further down, additional categories include "Lap desks" and "Travel tote bags," with a note indicating how many times each category has been viewed. The overall layout is clean and user-friendly, emphasizing easy navigation for shoppers.

screens.screen_desc:
The screenshot displays a shopping cart summary from an online store. The subtotal for the items is $55.99, and there are three items in the cart. A prominent yellow button invites the user to proceed to checkout. There is an option to send items as a gift, along with a checkbox to deselect all items. 

The first item listed is an "Amazon Basics - Laptop Stand for Desk," marked as a best seller with a price of $24.22, showing a 15% discount from the typical price of $28.49. The second item is a "WantGor Women Corduroy Tote Bag," priced at $14.95, with a note indicating it is in stock and has been purchased by over 1,000 customers in the past month. The interface includes options to delete or save items for later.

screens.user_guide: Tap delete button of first item

flow_desc: The user requests to cancel the most recently added item from their shopping cart. To fulfill this, they will first navigate to the shopping app interface by tapping the third tab at the bottom of the screen. Once in the shopping cart summary, they will see a list of items, including the most recently added "Amazon Basics - Laptop Stand for Desk." They will then tap the delete button associated with this item to remove it from their cart. This flow emphasizes a straightforward approach for users to manage their online shopping experience efficiently.
